Package org.oucs.oxpoints.entities Description

OxPointsEntitys are java representations of objects from the OxPoints ontology. For each class in the OxPoinits ontology there has to be a corresponding java representation. These OxPointsEntitys follow the convention of JavaBeans (see JavaBeans on Wikipedia) and can be dynamically generated from the corresponding RDF or used to create RDF.

Since adding new entities to the system should be a simple task, OxPointsEntitys are kept very simple. They only consist of get and set methods for each attribute that can be stored for that particular entity and additional annotations. These annotations are then used by the OxPoints system to either generate the entities from the RDF, to generate RDF from entities or to transform entities into a different output format (e.g. KML).
